      "writtenOn": "2026-06-15T06:29:01Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "from what I can see, systemd/sd-bus does throw org.freedesktop.DBus.Error.ObjectPathInUse when a vtable is registered at an already-taken D-Bus path. \nBut in phosphor-snmp, the object paths use an incrementing ID (lastClientId++), not something derived from address+port, so even duplicate clients would end up with different paths like /xyz/.../1, /xyz/.../2, and sd-bus would never detect the conflict.\n\nThe duplicate detection here is application-level logic (same address+port already configured), which sd-bus has no way to enforce on its own. That\u0027s the gap this error is meant to fill.",
      "parentUuid": "a0cda23c_26229b0d",
      "revId": "1e334515f703092f6106244aa622e8950be192b0",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
